00:23:14.140 --> 00:23:20.700
of the late 1970s, which initially Deng Xiaoping
thought this was a healthy expression of differences

00:23:20.700 --> 00:23:26.600
of opinion. Then when the people started talking
about Deng being a new dictator, he cracked

00:23:26.600 --> 00:23:32.410
down on it. But what interests me about it
here is one of the most famous wall posters

00:23:32.410 --> 00:23:40.160
that's well known, Wei Jingsheng who's now
one of the most famous dissidents in exile

00:23:40.160 --> 00:23:46.510
from China, was a political prisoner and then
left. He called for a fifth modernization.

00:23:46.510 --> 00:23:50.890
He said that China needed those four modernizations
that Deng was talking about, but it also needed

00:23:50.890 --> 00:23:58.170
a fifth, Democracy. Now that part's well known,
but what's sometimes forgotten, is that why

00:23:58.170 --> 00:24:03.790
he said, the argument he made for why China
needed democracy. He said because without

00:24:03.790 --> 00:24:10.220
it, the modernization drive and economic growth
will confront insurmountable obstacles. So

00:24:10.220 --> 00:24:14.200
he wasn't just saying a democracy an abstract
good. He's saying that without that China

00:24:14.200 --> 00:24:19.050
will not be able to have the economic growth
it needs. And now our conundrum is China has

00:24:19.050 --> 00:24:23.620
had this enormous economic growth without
having democracy. So it's a different setting

00:24:23.620 --> 00:24:27.580
than saying that China needs democracy to
become modern.

