00:27:37.720 --> 00:27:44.170
protest were saying we need a change in leadership
in order to become modern, which is what we

00:27:44.170 --> 00:27:50.710
desire. Now a lot of times the protests have
some edge to them of the way modernity is

00:27:50.710 --> 00:27:56.010
coming to us is effecting our lives in negative
as well as positives ways, or we should have

00:27:56.010 --> 00:28:01.210
a say in how we are brought into the modern
world. So even things that people desire,

00:28:01.210 --> 00:28:08.610
they want some control over, and this is something
we know from the United States and other places.

00:28:08.610 --> 00:28:13.480
2008 was a year that really changed the vision
of China from being thought of as a backward,

00:28:13.480 --> 00:28:17.750
to being thought of as a modern country, with
the technological displays in the stadiums

00:28:17.750 --> 00:28:23.780
in Beijing wowing the world. The first protests
of that year, took place in Shanghai, or one

00:28:23.780 --> 00:28:27.870
of the first protests. And it was against
the extension of the magnetic levitation train

00:28:27.870 --> 00:28:34.720
line, this super-fast train, through a neighborhood
in Shanghai, which the local residents, who

00:28:34.720 --> 00:28:38.520
are largely people who admired or liked the
fact that Shanghai had become this modern

00:28:38.520 --> 00:28:41.550
city again, said we don't want it running
through our neighborhood. It's going to bring

00:28:41.550 --> 00:28:46.520
down our housing prices, we're worried about
noise pollution, were worried about radiation

00:28:46.520 --> 00:28:51.920
effects that would harm our children. It was
described as one of the first not in my backyard

00:28:51.920 --> 00:28:57.400
or NIMBY protests in China. So the people
who were protesting were largely middleclass

00:28:57.400 --> 00:29:02.100
people, or new middleclass. They organized
via cell phone and instant messaging. These

00:29:02.100 --> 00:29:08.720
were not people who were against China modernizing,
but they wanted more control of how exactly

00:29:08.720 --> 00:29:11.251
it was modernized. They thought that with
this type of thing we should have some say,

00:29:11.251 --> 00:29:15.670
whether the government listens to us more.

00:29:15.670 --> 00:29:19.160
And they actually succeeded, at least for
a time, in stopping the extension of the train

00:29:19.160 --> 00:29:23.790
line. The year before there had been similar
kinds of protests in the city of Xiamen complaining

00:29:23.790 --> 00:29:29.350
of a chemical plant being brought nearby.
And this is the bigger protests of 2008 were

00:29:29.350 --> 00:29:34.600
in Tibet. There were big protests, and this
were often interpreted in the U.S. media as

00:29:34.600 --> 00:29:39.211
being all about religious freedom. And to
some extent, of course that's part of it.

00:29:39.211 --> 00:29:44.770
But there were also about economic grievances,
and they were also about a complaint about

00:29:44.770 --> 00:29:49.400
having a particular version of modernization
shoved down people's throat. Which people

00:29:49.400 --> 00:29:55.200
around the world never like to have happen.
So in Beijing, what is said about Tibet is

00:29:55.200 --> 00:30:02.970
often that Tibetans should be grateful, because
we've brought them modern schools and modern

00:30:02.970 --> 00:30:08.460
railways and we're linking them to the world.
What some Tibetans say, it's not that we're

00:30:08.460 --> 00:30:13.770
against those things, but we only want those
things in a process that is benefiting us

00:30:13.770 --> 00:30:19.300
as well as other groups that are living locally.
And we should have some say in how exactly

00:30:19.300 --> 00:30:24.630
these things are playing out. We want a more
responsive government. So the protests in

00:30:24.630 --> 00:30:27.600
Shanghai, the protests were radically different,
they were very different stories, but there

00:30:27.600 --> 00:30:37.140
was a connecting thread I think, in this kind
of concern with the impact on lives of a form

00:30:37.140 --> 00:30:44.031
of development that didn't have input from
the people being most affected. And so these

