00:44:48.690 --> 00:44:53.310
when you go there. So it's a very anomalous,
unusual situation that's lasted longer than

00:44:53.310 --> 00:45:00.410
a lot of us expected. The Chinese countryside,
the changes there have been just enormous.

00:45:00.410 --> 00:45:06.700
And I think the question for the future is
in part that a lot of the, a lot of rural

00:45:06.700 --> 00:45:13.810
areas have been left behind by the economic
booms and they've gotten some benefits from

00:45:13.810 --> 00:45:19.800
it in part by workers from the countryside
going to the cities, working to, the workers

00:45:19.800 --> 00:45:25.300
of this economic boom have largely been migrant
workers going to factory towns and sending

00:45:25.300 --> 00:45:32.290
their money back to the countryside. Uh, one
thing that's happened I think, the most important,

00:45:32.290 --> 00:45:38.900
two of the most important things to keep in
mind, one is the Chinese government has set

00:45:38.900 --> 00:45:44.900
itself up in promising that over the long
run life will get significantly better materially

00:45:44.900 --> 00:45:51.700
for all Chinese, but that some people will
get rich first. So there are people who haven't

00:45:51.700 --> 00:45:55.560
benefited as much from the economic reforms,
have maybe gotten just some small bits of

00:45:55.560 --> 00:46:01.190
improvement who are thinking their turn will
come eventually. This has made the Chinese

00:46:01.190 --> 00:46:06.500
government addicted to growth, high growth
rates. If economic growth, slowed, tapered

00:46:06.500 --> 00:46:11.780
off, or came to a stop, you'd have a lot of
very angry people, who are already maybe angry

00:46:11.780 --> 00:46:17.990
at, are angry at corruption and the unevenness
of the spread of wealth, of new wealth. But

00:46:17.990 --> 00:46:22.050
then would be furious. Because it wouldn't
be that they were waiting their turn, it would

00:46:22.050 --> 00:46:26.420
be that their turn would never come. So that's
I think something that concerns the Chinese

00:46:26.420 --> 00:46:33.020
government a great deal. It's why they've
begun to try to move toward meliorating the

00:46:33.020 --> 00:46:36.350
growing difference between rural and urban
prosperity.

00:46:36.350 --> 00:46:41.380
